The portable SDK for UPnP(tm) Devices (libupnp) provides developers
with an API and open source code for building control points, devices,
and bridges that are compliant with Version 1.0 of the Universal Plug
and Play Device Architecture Specification and support several operating
systems like Linux, *BSD, Solaris and others.

Pass STATIC=yes for static libraries; Pass IPV6=yes for ipv6 support.

This is legacy version for programs not supporting the new Libupnp ABI.

libupnp-legacy conflicts with the libupnp package.
